Governor Aminu Bello Masari of Katsina state has expressed his administration’s commitment to ensure the timely commencement of medicine courses at the Umaru Musa Yar’Adua University Katsina. Masari made this assertion when he received a high-powered delegation of the Medical and Dental Council of Nigeria on a visitation mission in preparation for the take-off of the course at the University. He said towards ensuring a hitch-free take off of the course, additional structures have been put in place at the Federal Medical Centre converted to a Federal Teaching hospital in the state. The Governor, however, maintained that the government is awaiting the report of the panel with a view to identifying where more commitments are required. Masari who is highly elated with the performance of the institution added that his administration is proud of the products of the university going on the records of its academic excellence. Dr. Tajudeen Sanusi, the Registrar of the council and leader of the delegation, earlier told the Governor that, they were in Katsina to assess facilities at the faculty of medicine Umaru Musa Yar’Adua University prior to the commencement of the programme. The Team Leader who was impressed with the facilities in place at the faculty promised to present a copy of the assessment report to the management of the institution.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ Dr. Bashir Usman Ruwan Godiya, the Special Adviser on Higher Education, on his part, said the team was conducted around the faculty of medicine UMYU, and the Federal Teaching Hospital Katsina.